You can do a simple inorder traversal of the tree.
```
int inorderTraversal(TrieNode* pNode)
{
	if (!pNode)
		return 0;

	int count = 0;
	for (int i = 0; i &lt; ALPHABET_SIZE; ++i)
		count += inorderTraversal(pNode-&gt;children[i]);

	return count + 1;
}
```

