You can read more on [Exception Chaining][1]. But, that&#39;s for Python 3


  [1]: https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-3134/

In Python 2, you can store your exception in a variable, then raise it again explicitly like this:

    try:
        do something
    except Exception as e:
        try:
            do something again
        except:
            pass
        raise e

